# Auth and Session Rules (Mandatory)

Use Better Auth with secure cookie sessions as the single auth model.

## Session model

- Use HTTP-only secure session cookies.
- Do not store auth tokens in `localStorage` or `sessionStorage`.
- All auth traffic must run over HTTPS/TLS in deployed environments.

## Frontend behavior

- Check session using `GET /api/auth/session` on app load.
- If any protected API call returns `401`, redirect user to login flow.
- Social login must use browser navigation to `GET /api/auth/social/{provider}` and not `fetch()`.

## Role routing baseline

- `couple` -> `/dashboard`
- `vendor` -> `/vendor/dashboard`
- `admin` -> `/admin/dashboard`

## Security behavior

- Never expose session internals in logs or client-visible debug messages.
- Enforce RBAC checks server-side for every protected endpoint.
